            "section1" => "According to the World Health Organization, tobacco use causes more than 8 million deaths each year, with approximately 1.2 million of those deaths being attributed to exposure to secondhand vape. Nicotine addiction, like heroin and cocaine addiction, has a high relapse rate, but the good news is that quitting vaping significantly improves health outcomes, even if you’ve smoked for many years.",
